</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but even I could not stop it. Luckily no collision of any kind happened.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What it did however was to lead me to investigate the O.E.M. tyres fitted to the car and others.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the main manufacturers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">( car</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and tyre) s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eem to focus on mpg,noise,and good wear miles. Non of which gives good </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">grip !</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Indeed the tyres fitted to my car and almost all the others I looked at were described by the tyre makers as 'SUMMER' </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tyres !</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> With many suggesting for 'Winter' you should fit 'W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inter' or 'All Weather / Season' tyres as the 'Summer' tyres performance falls off so sharply to a dangerous extent ( as I had found) in 'Winter' weather !</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There are many many graphs and tests that clearly demonstrate this on the internet. However in many</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> European countries it is not an issue because '</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Winter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ' tyres are a legal requirement so the issue never arises. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Here we neither have that legislation or a real understanding of seasonal tyre construction, hence the very real danger all road users are i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n from these totally inappropriate / dangerous </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tyres !</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I wonder how many people will die this winter in accidents that would not have happened had the car been fitted with the correct </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tyre ?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">How do car manufacturers ( who all recognize the need for 'Wint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">er' tyres and try to sell them at around Â£1000 a set !) get away with selling cars on tyres that are in reality only 'safe' and 'fit for purpose' in the spring/summer/autumn months and in 'Winter' are as much use as a handbrake on a canoe ! </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Should they n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ot fit 'All Weather' tyres that are safe 365 days of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">year ,whatever</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the weather !</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I do hope you will see and understand the need for strong urgent action to challenge this extremely serious safety issue.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>